==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Homomorphy
<hw>Ho"mo*mor`phy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets> + Gr. <grk>morfh`</grk> form.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Similarity of form; resemblance in external
characters, while widely different in fundamental structure; resemblance
in geometric ground form. See <er>Homophyly</er>,
<er>Promorphology</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Homonomous</ent>⟦br⟧
